						<div class="postbody">Care to enumerate the various levels of PPU accuracy? You can render the entire screen at once, which causes glitches for most games. You can render one scanline at a time, which works well for a majority of NES software. What does rendering one pixel at a time mean? Nintendulator accuracy, with all the internal shift registers and memory reads at specific times, or something less demanding? And is there something beyond this too (assuming Nintendulator isn't perfect)?</div>

